event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_02af6686bf2342b60169fb47ab92a08195b48a0e0a4276a9f0","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":267,"text":"Let t = hours after 3:00 pm when they meet (t ≥ 1).  \nDistance by train from Paris = 80t.  \nDistance by train from Lyon = 100(t − 1).  \nThey meet when 80t + 100(t − 1) = 470.\n\nSolve: 180t − 100 = 470 → 180t = 570 → t = 570/180 = 3 1/6 h = 3 h 10 min.\n\nSo they meet at 3:00 pm + 3 h 10 min = 6:10 pm.  \nDistance from Paris = 80 × 3.1666... = 253 1/3 km ≈ 253.33 km."}

